text.section:
The series shall notify its known claimants in writing of its dissolution at any time after the effective date of dissolution. The written notice shall:
Identify the series by such name or names as it used in transacting business and the name of the statutory trust;
Describe information that must be included in a claim;
Provide a mailing address where a claim may be sent;
State the deadline, which may not be fewer than one hundred twenty (120) days after the date of the written notice, by which the series must receive the claim; and
State that the claim will be barred if not received by the deadline.
